subSection.paragraph:
Deltocephalinae Dallas, 1870 stands out as the most diverse subfamily of Cicadellidae Van Duzee, 1916 , with 7,134 species of phloem feeding leafhoppers recorded across the world, encompassing nearly one-third of the family’s total diversity ( Zahniser & Dietrich 2013 ;
Dai et al . 2017
;
Cao et al . 2022
).

Among the 39 tribes of the subfamily, 
Bahitini
Zahniser & Dietrich, 2013
currently comprises 26 genera and 188 species found exclusively on the New World (
Zahniser & Dietrich 2013
; 
Camisão & Takiya 2017
; 
Camisão & Dietrich 2022
).

